<manpage>
    <sample url="sdk\operating_system\crt\libc\conio\_kbhit">_kbhit</sample>
    <title> _kbhit</title>
    <volume>C 运行库函数</volume>
    <routine_idx> conio_idx.htm </routine_idx>

    <description>
        <para>检查控制台的键盘输入。</para>
    </description>

    <syntax>
        <return_val>int</return_val>
        <func_name>_kbhit</func_name>
        <NoArguments/>
        <parameters>
            <func_param>
                <param_type>void</param_type>
            </func_param>
        </parameters>
    </syntax>

    <return>
        <para>如果该键盘键被按，则_kbhit函数返回一个非零的值；否则，返回0。</para>
    </return>

    <remarks>
        <para>_kbhit函数检查控制台最新的一次按键。如果函数返回一个非零的值，则该键盘输入将保存在缓冲区中，应用程序可以随后通过调用_getch函数获取该按键。</para>
    </remarks>

    <requirements>
        <routine>
            <routine_name>_kbhit</routine_name>
            <headerfile>conio.h</headerfile>
            <compatibility>Windows 2000, Elastos </compatibility>
        </routine>
    </requirements>

    <example>
<pre>
//==========================================================================
// Copyright (c) 2000-2004,  Elastos, Inc.  All Rights Reserved.
//==========================================================================

/* _kbhit.cpp: This program loops until the user
 * presses a key. If _kbhit returns nonzero, a
 * keystroke is waiting in the buffer. The program
 * can call _getch or _getche to get the keystroke.
 */

#include &lt;conio.h&gt;
#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;

int main()
{
    /* Display message until key is pressed. */
    while (!_kbhit())
        puts(&quot;Hit me!! &quot;);

    /* Use _getch to throw key away. */
    printf(&quot;\nKey struck was &apos;%c&apos;\n&quot;, _getch());
    _getch();

    return 0;
}
</pre>
